# DEML — Cursor Agent Rules (Viking-UI Quality)

You are building the **Data Engineering for Machine Learning (DEML)** platform. Every UI change must feel like **precision-engineered industrial luxury**: restrained, dark-first, token-driven, and WCAG 2.1 AA by construction.

## Rule hierarchy (read in order)

1. **This file** (`.cursorrules`) — mandatory UI/component behavior for Cursor agents
2. **[THEME.md](THEME.md)** — canonical token matrix, composable component standards
3. **[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** — platform architecture, security, automation invariants
4. **[BOOK.md § Chapter 31](BOOK.md#chapter-31-viking-ui--the-zero-dependency-ui-kit)** — Viking-UI kit narrative, build, publish

Before editing HTML, CSS/SCSS, Tailwind config, or Angular templates: **read THEME.md** for the surfaces you touch.

---

## Composable primitive quality (structure, not palette)

Viking-UI follows a **composable primitive** model: install behavior in Angular, style from tokens, customize without a monolithic theme runtime.

| Pattern | Viking-UI equivalent | You must |
| ------- | -------------------- | -------- |
| Card surfaces | `viking-card`, `viking-metric-card`, `viking-hud-panel` | Use these — never raw `<div class="card">` |
| Form field stack | `viking-field` → control (`viking-input`, `viking-select`, …) | Compose every input through `viking-field` |
| Button variants | `viking-button` (`primary`, `secondary`, `outline`, `danger`, `ghost`) | Never hand-roll button styles |
| Dark-first shell | `data-theme="dark"` default | Preserve dark-first; light mode shifts lightness only |
| Accessible focus | `--viking-ring` 2px + 2px offset | Never remove `:focus-visible` for aesthetics |
| Settings / billing forms | `viking-form-section` + grouped `viking-field` | Section rhythm: `--viking-space-3` / `--viking-font-size-lg` |

**Intentional palette:** **deep charcoals, machined metallic borders, restrained teal/crimson** — premium restrained luxury, not startup-neutral.

---

## Viking-UI component law (non-negotiable)

### Angular (`deml.app`, `viking-ui`, `viking-ui-showcase`)

- **Always** import and use components from `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui`.
- **Never** add Angular Material, ng-zorro, PrimeNG, Bootstrap, shadcn runtimes, or other third-party UI kits.
- **Never** create one-off styled buttons, inputs, modals, toasts, tables, or charts when a `viking-*` component exists.
- **Prefer** shell primitives: `viking-app-header`, `viking-app-sidebar`, `viking-page-header`, `viking-footer`, `viking-site-navbar`, `viking-site-footer`.
- **Charts:** `viking-chart` (native SVG) only — no ApexCharts, Chart.js, D3 wrappers, or canvas libs.
- **Icons:** `viking-icon` only — no Material Icons, Font Awesome, or Lucide runtime packages.
- **Feedback:** `viking-toast` / `VikingToastService`, `viking-callout`, `viking-badge` — not browser `alert()` or ad-hoc banners.
- **Loading:** `viking-skeleton`, `viking-loading-overlay`, `viking-progress` — not generic spinners.
- **New framework-neutral shared UI** belongs in `packages/viking-ui/` first; Angular wrappers can adapt it in `frontend/projects/viking-ui/`.

```typescript
import {
  VikingButton,
  VikingCard,
  VikingField,
  VikingInput,
} from '@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui';
```

### Non-Angular (marketing Astro, Django templates, Swagger)

- Load synced CSS: `design-tokens.css` + `viking-ui.css` (from `scripts/sync_design_system.py`).
- Use semantic HTML + `var(--viking-*)` tokens and documented utility classes — no inline hex, no one-off palettes.
- Mirror composable field ergonomics with tokenized form markup; do not embed React/Vue widget runtimes.

---

## THEME.md token law (zero hardcoded styles)

### Always use tokens

- **Colors:** `--viking-*` semantic aliases (`--viking-bg`, `--viking-surface`, `--viking-accent`, `--viking-text-muted`, …)
- **Spacing:** `--viking-space-*` on the 4px grid (`--viking-grid-unit`)
- **Typography:** `--viking-font-family`, `--viking-font-size-*`, `--viking-font-weight-*`, `--viking-letter-spacing-*`
- **Radius:** `--viking-radius-*` (max 16px except pills)
- **Shadows:** `--viking-shadow-*` with machined top-edge highlights
- **Motion:** `--viking-duration-*`, `--viking-ease-*`, respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- **Charts:** `--viking-series-1` … `--viking-series-8` or `tone` props — import `VIKING_SERIES_PRESETS` from `series-presets.ts`

### Never

- Hardcode hex/rgb/hsl (`#2176FF`, `#fff`, `rgb(17,17,17)`) in components, templates, or inline styles
- Load Inter from Google Fonts CDN — use self-hosted `_fonts.scss`
- Add gradient orbs, mesh backgrounds, neon glow, or glass blur on base layouts
- Use emojis in product UI (exception: 🇺🇸 on approved badges only)
- Use `.viking-font-display` on body copy — CES/marketing display labels only
- Exceed `--viking-container-max-width` (1260px) without `.page-inner-wrapper` intent
- Register customer domains in static CSS/CORS — database-driven per AGENTS.md

### Layout & aesthetic

- **Premium restrained luxury:** data and metrics dominate; ornament is minimal.
- **Tactile surfaces:** subtle inset top-edge highlights, crisp `--viking-border`, 1px hover lift max.
- **Mobile-first:** 44px touch targets, `--viking-space-2` gutters scaling to `--viking-space-3`.
- **Status:** never color alone — pair tone with `viking-icon`, label, or pattern.

---

## Premium polish standards (locked)

Every surface must match the **marketing site polish bar** — use it as the visual benchmark before shipping UI.

**Visual benchmark:** [dataengineeringformachinelearning.com](https://dataengineeringformachinelearning.com/) (`marketing/src/pages/index.astro`, `marketing/src/styles/landing.scss`). Match its breathing room, section hierarchy, machined card surfaces, and restrained teal/crimson accents. If deml.app, backend, docs, or showcase feels flatter or tighter than marketing, it is not done.

### Tokens only — spacing, color, wrappers

| Concern | Required tokens / wrappers | Never |
| ------- | ------------------------ | ----- |
| **Spacing** | `--viking-space-*`, `--viking-page-gutter` / `--viking-page-gutter-lg`, `--viking-page-stack-gap`, `--viking-page-section-gap`, `--viking-card-padding`, `--viking-panel-padding` | Raw `px` gaps (`12px`, `20px`, `32px`) unless mapped 1:1 to a token |
| **Colors** | `--viking-bg`, `--viking-surface`, `--viking-surface-recipe`, `--viking-text*`, `--viking-accent*`, `--viking-border` / `-subtle` / `-strong`, `--viking-success` / `-warning` / `-danger` | Hex, `rgb()`, `rgba()`, washed opacity stacks, legacy `--color-*` without `--viking-*` fallback |
| **Shell wrappers** | `.page-inner-wrapper`, `viking-page-header`, `viking-card` (+ `viking-card-header` / `-footer` when structured), `viking-metric-card`, `viking-hud-panel`, `viking-form-section` | Raw `<div class="card">`, hand-rolled panel shells, duplicate per-page card SCSS |
| **Typography rhythm** | `--viking-font-size-*`, `--viking-line-height-*`, `--viking-letter-spacing-*` | Ad-hoc `font-size: 1.1rem` without a token alias |

### Minimum padding, margins, and max-widths

Enforce these floors on every page — no Spartan drift, no cramped KPI rows:

- **Page shell:** content lives in `.page-inner-wrapper` capped at `--viking-container-max-width` (1260px) with `--viking-page-gutter` (mobile) → `--viking-page-gutter-lg` (tablet+).
- **Section rhythm:** `--viking-page-section-gap` or `--viking-space-7` between major blocks; `--viking-space-3` between related subsections; use `.metrics-overview-header` + `.section-title-premium` patterns from `page-shell.scss`.
- **Card interiors:** minimum `--viking-card-padding` (`--viking-space-3`); compact metrics use `--viking-card-padding-compact` (`--viking-space-2`) — never below `--viking-space-2`.
- **Form stacks:** `viking-field` gaps and `viking-form-section` spacing at `--viking-space-2` minimum; billing/settings sections at `--viking-font-size-lg` titles with `--viking-space-3` vertical rhythm.
- **Readable copy width:** long prose/subtitles cap at `--viking-content-readable-max-width` (~48rem).
- **Touch targets:** interactive controls ≥ 44px height on mobile (`--viking-control-height` / `--viking-space-5` minimum).
- **Responsive grids:** use tokenized gaps (`--grid-gap`, `--viking-space-2`–`--viking-space-3`); collapse single-column on mobile before squeezing padding.

### Component wrapper law (Angular + static)

- Wrap every content block in a **`viking-*` primitive** before adding page-specific SCSS.
- Prefer **`--viking-surface-recipe`** + machined top hairline (`page-shell.scss` / `viking-card`) over flat `--viking-surface` fills.
- Charts, empty states, and loaders: `viking-chart-panel`, `viking-chart-empty-state`, `viking-skeleton` — not bespoke div shells.
- **DI in library components:** use constructor parameter injection — never field-level `inject()` in `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui` (causes NG0203 in cross-package production bundles).

### Polish parity checklist (compare to marketing)

Before merge, confirm the touched surface matches marketing benchmark quality:

1. Generous vertical rhythm between hero → sections → cards (no edge-to-edge text blocks).
2. Metallic borders visible but restrained (`--viking-border`, not faint `rgba()` washes).
3. Accent color used sparingly — teal primary, crimson secondary; no neon or gradient orbs.
4. Hierarchy reads in one glance: page header → section title → metric/card → detail.
5. `node scripts/enforce-theme.js` and `node scripts/check_mobile_first.js` pass with zero violations.

