## Static CSS build pipeline (single owner)

| Role | Path |
| ---- | ---- |
| **Canonical SCSS** | `packages/viking-ui/src/styles/` (tokens, components, navbar, bundle) |
| **Static CSS build** | `packages/viking-ui/scripts/build-css.mjs` → `packages/viking-ui/dist/` |
| **Fan-out to surfaces** | `python scripts/sync_design_system.py` (marketing, backend, frontend `/assets/`) |

**Do not** recreate `packages/deml-design-system` or `frontend/src/design-system/` mirrors. Railway/Docker frontend builds compile live SCSS from viking-ui only — no monorepo-root paths.

---

## Pre-ship UI checklist

1. All interactive UI uses `viking-*` components (or tokenized static markup on non-Angular surfaces).
2. No hardcoded colors, spacing, or font sizes outside `--viking-*` tokens.
3. Padding, gutters, and max-widths meet **Premium polish standards** — parity with marketing benchmark.
4. `node scripts/run_axe.js` passes (WCAG 2.1 AA).
5. Token changes start in `packages/viking-ui/src/styles/_variables.scss`, then `npm run build:viking-ui:package` + `python scripts/sync_design_system.py`.
6. Doc changes to design governance update **THEME.md**, **AGENTS.md**, **BOOK.md Ch.31**, and **README.md** together.
7. `npm run test:viking-ui` and app `npm test` pass for touched surfaces (charts, auth, forms, icons).
8. `node scripts/enforce-theme.js` reports zero violations before merge.

---

## Automated enforcement (run before commit)

| Gate | Command | Blocks |
| ---- | ------- | ------ |
| Theme tokens / no hardcoding | `node scripts/enforce-theme.js` | Off-palette hex, legacy Lab Coat vars, Material classes, generic `.card`/`.btn-*` |
| Accessibility | `node scripts/run_axe.js` | WCAG 2.1 AA violations on HTML/Astro |
| Mobile-first layout | `node scripts/check_mobile_first.js` | Missing `.page-inner-wrapper`, sub-44px touch targets |
| Lint | `cd frontend && npm run lint` | ESLint / angular-eslint |
| Viking-UI tests | `cd frontend && npm run test:viking-ui` | Regressions in charts, forms, icons, auth panel |
| Full quality | `uvx pre-commit run --all-files` | All pre-commit hooks |

Apply safe theme auto-fixes: `node scripts/enforce-theme.js --apply`

---

## Testing requirements (key surfaces)

Every change to these areas **must** include or update Vitest coverage:

| Surface | Location | What to test |
| ------- | -------- | ------------ |
| Charts | `projects/viking-ui/src/lib/chart/` | SVG path generation, bar/line/donut kinds, zoom/pan window math (`chart-zoom.spec.ts`) |
| Auth flows | `src/app/services/auth.service.spec.ts`, `lib/auth-panel/` | Login/logout/checkAuth signals, OAuth panel a11y, social button emits |
| Forms | `lib/field/`, `lib/input/`, `lib/form-section/` | CVA/ngModel, required/error states, section layout classes |
| Icons | `lib/core/icons.ts`, `lib/icon/` | Registry resolution, Material aliases, size presets, semantic color tokens, brand marks |

Run library tests: `npm run test:viking-ui` (uses `vitest.viking-ui.config.ts` — real templates, not stubbed).

---

## Performance & minimalism (Starship-grade)

Build like reusable flight hardware — every line earns its mass:

- **OnPush + signals** on all Viking-UI components; avoid mutable state and unnecessary re-renders.
- **Zero-dep charts/icons** — native SVG only; no canvas, D3, Chart.js, or icon font runtimes.
- **Pure helpers** — extract testable math (chart zoom, icon resolution) into standalone modules; keep components thin.
- **No speculative abstractions** — one composable primitive beats three wrapper layers.
- **Lazy by default** — route-level code splitting in the app; no eager imports of showcase-only components.
- **Token-only styling** — CSS variables compile once; no runtime theme engines or CSS-in-JS.
- **Reusable first** — new UI belongs in `frontend/projects/viking-ui/` before app-specific forks.

---

## Hard rejections (never ship)

- Third-party UI kits (Material, Bootstrap, PrimeNG, shadcn runtimes, Font Awesome, Lucide runtime packages).
- Hardcoded hex/rgb/hsl in templates, SCSS, or inline styles (except `_variables.scss` / `_series-colors.scss`).
- Hand-rolled buttons, inputs, modals, toasts, tables, or charts when `viking-*` exists.
- `alert()`, generic spinners, color-only status, gradient orbs, neon glow, glass blur on base layouts.
- Google Fonts CDN for Inter — use self-hosted `_fonts.scss`.
- Pickle for ML models; hardcoded tenant domains in CORS; `"platform"` string FKs in workers.

---

## Platform invariants (from AGENTS.md — do not break)

- Event Projections: Outbox, idempotency, versioned events
- Symmetrical multi-tenant workers: `Tenant.objects.all()` — no hardcoded Tenant0 exceptions
- UUID PKs everywhere; no pickle for ML models
- Dynamic CORS via database registration
- Run `uvx pre-commit run --all-files` before committing

When architectural UI patterns change, update **BOOK.md** first, then sync via `scripts/sync_content.py`.
